# Xenoblade decompilation (auto)

> **Source of truth:** `.claude/skills/xenoblade-decomp/SKILL.md`. This rule is a
> mirror for Cursor; keep it in sync with the `.claude` copy.

At the **start of every task** in this repository:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/xenoblade-decomp/SKILL.md` and follow it.
2. Consult `PLAN.md` before changing gameplay, render, input, or memory behavior.
3. Use `tools/coop/run.py` for build/diff/cycle loops — do not improvise a separate pipeline.

**Policy:** all decompilation targets require **`FULL_MATCH`** until the policy in `coop.json` / `PLAN.md` is revised.

**MWCC reference:** read `docs/MWCC_REFERENCE.md` for matching work; **append reusable patterns and breakthroughs** there when you find them (not only in `attempts.jsonl`).

**Source language:** decompilation output is **high-level C/C++ only** — no asm, `.s`, register variables, or stack-offset tricks in `src/**` / `libs/**` (retail asm is reference-only).

When editing `src/**`, `libs/**`, or `configure.py`, run `coop run cycle` or `coop run diff` for the affected unit before claiming a target is complete.

**Split object size:** decomp `.text` must fit the retail split slice (`config/<region>/splits.txt`). Run `python tools/coop/run.py size <unit>` — `diff`, `cycle`, and `behaviour compare` also print a `size:` line and fail when over budget.

**Below 100% static match:** register and pass `python tools/coop/run.py behaviour compare <test-id>` with extensive host scenarios (see `tools/test/compare_behaviour/README.md`). Run `behaviour audit` before claiming `BEHAVIOR_VERIFIED`.
